## Cisco PSIRT plugin for [Errbot](https://errbot.io)

## Configuration
In order to use bot you need to install it from errbot with `!repos install https://github.com/btotharye/err-cisco-psirt.git`

After installing you can then do `!plugin config psirt` to get the output and see the order you need to specify your credentials in:

```
!plugin config psirt {'CLIENT_ID': 'client id here', 'CLIENT_SECRET': 'client secret here'}
```

You can get a client ID and secret from signing up for the API at https://apiconsole.cisco.com/apps/myapis under the PSIRT application.

### About
[Errbot](http://errbot.io) is a python chatbot, this plugin answers questions about Cisco Open Vulnerabilities (PSIRT)

### Installation
From errbot issue command: `!repos install https://github.com/btotharye/err-cisco-psirt.git`
